description:
Manwich Sloppy Joe Sauce is naturally thick and made with vine-ripened tomatoes, sweet onions, bell peppers and a special blend of spices and seasonings.

Directions
Easy as: 1. Brown 1 lb lean ground beef (or 3/4 lb ground turkey) in large skillet until no longer pink; drain. 2. Stir in 1 can Manwich; heat through. 3. Serve on hamburger buns. Out of hamburger buns? Serve on hot dog buns, toasted bread, bagels, biscuits or English muffins. Also tastes great over pasta, rice, or baked potato.

description:
Packed in USA.

Directions:

Prep Time: 5 minutes. Cook Time: 15 minutes. Makes 8 servings. You Will Need: 1 pkg. McCormick Seasoning Mix; 1 lb. lean ground beef or turkey; 1 can (6 oz) tomato paste (Substitution: Use 1 can (15 oz.) tomato sauce in place of tomato paste and water.); 1-1/4 cups water; 8 hamburger buns. 1. Brown meat in large skillet on medium-high heat. Drain fat. 2. Stir in Seasoning Mix, tomato paste and water. 3. Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve in rolls.

description:
Kids and adults agree, these are the Best Sloppy Joes in town.

Directions
Serves 4. 10 min.
Needs: 1 pound ground beef chuck; 1 pouch Red Fork Best Sloppy Joe Skillet Sauce; 1 can (8 ounces) tomato sauce or 1 can (15 ounces) crushed fire-roasted tomatoes.

Stove top:
1. Brown: Cook beef in a 10- or 12-inch nonstick skillet over high heat, stirring often, until nicely browned and cooked, 6 to 8 minutes. 2. Simmer and Serve: Stir in sauce and tomatoes. Simmer gently over low heat, stirring often, about 10 minutes. Season with salt to taste. Serve piled on soft rolls or hamburger buns. Variation: Substitute ground turkey for beef.
title: Red Fork Best Sloppy Joe Skillet Sauce 8 oz
